Follow these specifications to install an alarm siren:
Find a mounting area under the hood of your truck, at least 18 inches (46 cm) away from sources of extreme heat (exhaust manifolds, heater cores and radiators) and high in the engine compartment. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0d\/Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/0\/0d\/Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/aid1394053-v4-728px-Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Face the siren speaker downward, so as to avoid water damage. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/66\/Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/6\/66\/Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/aid1394053-v4-728px-Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Depending on your truck's make and model, you may also choose to mount the alarm system siren in your truck's inner fender, if you feel that area is even harder for a potential thief to reach. Determine what is behind the surface you plan on mounting the siren to, making sure there are no lines, cables or wires that your screws will go into. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/06\/Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet4.jpg\/v4-459px-Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/0\/06\/Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet4.jpg\/aid1394053-v4-728px-Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Use metal screws or nuts and bolts to mount the siren to your chosen surface. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/cc\/Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet5.jpg\/v4-459px-Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/c\/cc\/Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet5.jpg\/aid1394053-v4-728px-Install-a-Car-Alarm-in-a-Truck-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

